#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:13
msgid "The Invisible East Corpus"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:14
msgid "What is the Invisible East corpus?"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:16
msgid ""
"As of May 2025 the IEDC consists of 1182 documents including 367 transcribed "
"and 178 transcribed and translated into English."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:18
msgid "What kinds of texts are preserved here digitally?"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:20
msgid ""
"An estimated ninety percent of the IEDC fragments come from documents: "
"letters, legal deeds, lists, accounts, state documents and other everyday "
"writings and ephemera."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:21
msgid ""
"The remaining ten percent are coming from long-form literary texts, "
"including liturgy, Hebrew Bible, rabbinic literature,  medicine, astronomy,  "
"lexicography, poetry and theology."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:22
msgid ""
"During this period, paper, parchment, and other writing materials were "
"frequently reused. This practice often resulted in two entirely unrelated "
"texts being written on the front (recto) and back (verso) of the same piece "
"of paper, parchment, or other writing support. In our corpus, if the recto "
"and verso are connected or if the verso is left blank, the document is "
"assigned a single shelfmark, e.g. 'Ms.Heb.8333.99.' Conversely, when the "
"recto and verso are unrelated, each side is given its own distinct "
"shelfmark, e.g. 'Ms.Heb.8333.67recto' and 'Ms.Heb.8333.67verso'."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:24
msgid "Where were the IEDC texts written?"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:26
msgid "All the texts survived in Iran, Afghanistan and Central Asia."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:28
msgid "When is the material from?"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:30
msgid ""
"The majority of IEDC documents date to the period between 737 and 1221 CE."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:32
msgid "Where are the IEDC texts now?"
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:34
msgid ""
"The IEDC texts can now be found in around 12 libraries and private "
"collections in Europe, Afghanistan, Central Asia, Russia and China."
msgstr ""

#: general/templates/general/about-faqs.html:36
msgid "For more, see"
msgstr ""

